        <h2>About the Project</h2>
        <p>
            The Dolphin vs Shark Detector is an AI-powered tool that uses advanced image classification techniques to distinguish between dolphins and sharks. Built with AlexNet, this model leverages cutting-edge deep learning to aid in marine conservation and education.
        </p>
        <h2>Mission Statement</h2>
        <p>
            To leverage AI for identifying marine species, enabling better wildlife conservation and monitoring, and empowering ecotourism and research efforts worldwide.
        </p>
        <h2>Features</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Custom-trained AlexNet model for dolphin and shark classification.</li>
            <li>Dataset with diverse marine life images.</li>
            <li>85% validation accuracy on unseen data.</li>
            <li>Applications in marine research, ecotourism, and education.</li>
        </ul>
        <h2>How It Works</h2>
        <p>
            Upload an image of a dolphin or shark to our model, which analyzes the features and predicts the species with high accuracy.
        </p>
